Name: Basher
Description: A towering triple-barrelled turret manned by three tiny fires. Locks onto Navis and fires dangerous explosive rounds.

Name: Beetank
Description: Beetanks are short and stout artillery units that scuttle about before lining up their arcing explosive shots. They don’t need line of sight on a target to fire a barrage.

Name: Boomer
Description: Boomers fire the massive boomerang they carry in their jaws, which flies around the arena and back to their maw.

Name: Catack
Description: Catack Viruses ride around in tiny tanks, firing their devastating cannons at whatever gets in their sights.

Name: Canodumb
Description: These mounted turrets track enemies with their holographic reticules. They can be mounted on ceilings, floors, and even walls.

Name: Flicker
Description: Flicker Viruses look like geometric rainbow birds. They flit about, launch storms of feathers, and manipulate their songs to mimic voices.

Name: Handy
Description: Handy Viruses meld into floors, walls, and ceilings, disappearing and reappearing elsewhere with bombs at hand.

Name: HardHead
Description: HardHead Viruses lob element-spreading shells. Their color changes with their ammo.

Name: HutHike
Description: A barrel-chested quarterback Virus. When it’s not kicking explosive footballs, it’s throwing anyone and anything at its enemies.

Name: KillPlant
Description: KillPlants are tall Viruses that spit huge seeds. After a delay, the seeds explode.

Name: InstallWizard
Description: InstallWizards are pesky Viruses in starry robes that get up to trouble and then slip away by dazzling and distracting their victims.

Name: KillerEye
Description: KillerEye Viruses are deadly sentries that fire paralyzing lasers from their eye.

Name: Metrid
Description: A faceless wizard in a white and red robe. It hides from sight and summons meteor storms over enemies with its magical staff.

Name: Needler
Description: Needlers are robotic Viruses that scoot around on four suction-cupped legs, skittering up walls and across ceilings.

Name: NinJoy
Description: NinJoy Viruses are short and stout. They sneak up on targets, raining kunai on them or warping behind them for a slice.

Name: Pengi
Description: Pengi Viruses slide around on their bellies and fire massive snowflake attacks from their beaks.

Name: Piranha
Description: Piranhas are floating fish-like Viruses that attack with burst-fire harpoons from their mouths.

Name: Ratty
Description: Ratty Viruses move erratically, firing homing rat bombs. They move much faster when damaged.

Name: Shrimpy
Description: Shrimpy Viruses seal things in bubbles and spit bouncing bubble bombs at targets.

Name: Spikey
Description: Spikeys are fierce, chaotic Viruses that throw speedy fireballs from their mouths.

Name: BugTank
Description: BugTanks are short and stout artillery units that scuttle about before lining up their data-corrupting shots.

Name: Boingo
Description: Boingo Viruses are tiny imps with a massive springboard hat. They warp under people and objects and send them flying into the sky.

Name: Bunny
Description: Bunnys are cute Viruses that hop about and fire paralyzing rings from between their ears.

Name: CandleLight
Description: A fancy chandelier Virus with big, bright eyes. Plays with light to blind enemies or leave them stumbling in the dark.

Name: Flashy
Description: Viruses with lightbulb-esque heads that flit about at high speed before blinding their targets with strobing light.

Name: JoyRide
Description: A happy little Virus that tosses magic teleporting hula-hoops around. Is it just playing...?

Name: Mushy
Description: Mushy Viruses wiggle around, spreading noxious spores, and hopping about with surprising agility.

Name: MuteAnt
Description: MuteAnt Viruses are cold gray trumpet Viruses. They play cacophonic tunes to make Navis miserable.

Name: Number
Description: Number Viruses look like glassy, shining pillars. They lock Navis into dangerous places and put extra pressure on fights.

Name: ScriptKid
Description: ScriptKid Viruses look like neon goats with emoticon faces. Troublemaker punks, they mess with systems for the fun of it.

Name: Shadow
Description: Shadow Viruses are devious and devilish, assuming the faces and powers of others. Their cunning demonstrates an intelligence beyond most other Viruses.

Name: Skimmer
Description: A bag-shaped Virus with spider legs. The more Zenny it stores after skimming a transaction, the louder it jingles as it runs.

Name: Sparky
Description: Mechanical balls sparking with electricity, Sparky Viruses swerve erratically before slamming into targets.

Name: Spidy
Description: Expert web browsers, the sneaky Spidy Viruses set up sticky traps before pouncing on their prey.

Name: Spoofi
Description: A neon-blue caterpillar Virus that hides from sight. It tweaks how variables display, confusing Navis without actually changing anything.

Name: Spooky
Description: Spooky Viruses create paranormal pandemonium with spectral voices and big spooks.

Name: SwanGarde
Description: Bird fencers in yellow armor, SwanGardes use their rapier-like beaks to zap targets and disable their BattleChips. They honk loudly.

Name: UFO
Description: UFO Viruses fly on cute saucers, scanning enemy Folders and copying their chips.

Name: VoxUnpopuli
Description: The snake-like VoxUnpopuli hides from sight and uses vocal trickery to make Navis “say” embarrassing/confusing/antagonistic things.

Name: YeeHopper
Description: YeeHoppers are cute frog Viruses in cowboy hats. They ride Navis around like bucking broncos. They also ribbit “howdy.”

Name: Cactikil
Description: Cactikil Viruses are rooted in place. They toss their rolling, spikey heads at enemies.

Name: Champy
Description: Champy Viruses are speedy, blazing boxers with a nasty sucker punch.

Name: Cragger
Description: Colossal golem Viruses, Craggers hide in stone formations, breaking out to bash some heads. Rumors say they eat Mystery Data.

Name: Draggin
Description: Draggins are spritely draconic Viruses that dash into groups of enemies and burn them all with their bursts of flames.

Name: Drixol
Description: Drixol Viruses sail through the air, drilling through space in order to ambush Navis with their whirling drill heads.

Name: EleBall
Description: Eleball Viruses bounce through the air and attack with swirling balls of electricity.

Name: EleBee
Description: Elebees are quick wasp-like Viruses that flit about before warping behind their prey and skewering them with their stinger.

Name: Flamey
Description: A flying, flaming Virus that slams into targets and objects with its body, burning enemies and bursting through obstacles.

Name: Fishy
Description: Fishy are aerodynamic Viruses that fly at top speed, slamming Navis and slicing them with their razor fins.

Name: Fishy2
Description: Fishy2 are red-hot flying Viruses that trade extreme speed for trails of fire.

Name: Flappy
Description: Flappy Viruses flit about, hopping to and fro, before transforming into enormous statues that smash into the ground.

Name: Gaia
Description: A towering, hammer-wielding statue. It turns to stone when not attacking. Its hammer sends devastating shockwaves at foes.

Name: Hopper
Description: A small frog Virus in a huge shoe, Hoppers arc through the air and stomp on enemy heads with a loud ribbit.

Name: Miramira
Description: Animated shining armor, Miramira Viruses use their mirror shields to reflect projectiles and harness reflections of Navi Powers.

Name: Mosquirto
Description: Mosquirto Viruses buzz about and suck the life out of Navis with a needle-like proboscis. They can inject their allies with stolen energy.

Name: Quaker
Description: Quakers are hefty Viruses that leap into the air before slamming down, releasing shockwaves and stunning nearby Navis.

Name: Snaggit
Description: Snaggit Viruses look like tiny fox thieves. They hijack elements to protect themselves as they swipe foes with nasty claws.

Name: SnakeArm
Description: SnakeArm Viruses are burrowing sand worms. They drag their targets into the sand with their mighty maws.

Name: Swordy
Description: Knight-like Viruses that slide along the ground, halt foes in their tracks, and dispatch them with dramatic slices.

Name: Zomon
Description: Zomon are samurai-styled Viruses that dazzle enemies with their masterful sword slashes.

Name: 10Hut
Description: These militant Viruses look like two boots under a huge beret. They supply their allies with military tech and shout booming commands.

Name: Appley
Description: Beefy-looking worm Viruses in apple armor, Appleys assist other Viruses with fruity heals and macho encouragement.

Name: BestPlate
Description: BestPlate appears as a super-shiny plate of armor with a large, bushy mustache. It teleports onto Viruses to defend them.

Name: BuildaBees
Description: A team of three bees with construction gear that assemble simple structures (laden in honey) with lightning efficiency.

Name: Dominerd
Description: Dominerd Viruses hide from sight, revealing themselves to punish attackers.

Name: Floshell
Description: A cannonball-hurling mechanical lizard with a massive iron shield it can raise or lower. It can protect allies behind its shield.

Name: Heartstring
Description: A smiling harp, Heartstring Viruses link to other Viruses to keep them in tip-top shape.

Name: HyperCamera
Description: HyperCamera Viruses are winged, fist-sized bugs with camera bodies that scan for intruders. Their wings always make a buzzing noise.

Name: JetSet
Description: A pair of rockets with grabby arms, JetSet picks up its allies to arc them through the air.

Name: LifeTree
Description: A towering tree with an old, graven face. It twists and extends its roots to create barricades and reinforce allies.

Name: Loven
Description: Loven Viruses are pink ovens with legs and aprons. They bake elements into confections that heal their allies and burn foes.

Name: Manneking
Description: A mannequin-like Virus in ostentatious, setting-appropriate clothes. Strikes fashionable poses while nobody’s looking.

Name: MiniMercs
Description: A squad of soldiers only a foot tall, they coordinate with other Viruses for maximum firepower.

Name: Peppery
Description: The Appley Virus’s distant cousin invigorates other Viruses with its spicy nature.

Name: PopUp
Description: A visually and physically obstructive Virus that tries to steal your attention. Pay some Zenny and it leaves you alone... for now.

Name: Quicksilver
Description: A blob of liquid silver with a pair of leather goggles. It slips about and reconfigures Viruses, itself included.

Name: Tricki
Description: A short, impish-looking Virus with a crystalline body, Trickis make deceptive doubles of their allies.

Name: Trumpy
Description: Trumpy Viruses hop about, charge up, and then let loose a fanfare to aid its allies.

Name: Wandy
Description: Two floating white gloves. When it taps Viruses with its wand, poof! They look like mundane objects which undisguise when they attack.

Name: ZipZap
Description: A sparkball with aviator goggles, ZipZap Viruses fly chaotically, spreading electric circuitry, distracting enemies, and speeding up allies.

Name: Astronaughty
Description: A small green Virus in a space suit uses its power over gravity to aid allies or hinder opponents. Its helmet is incredibly fragile.

Name: BombCorn
Description: BombCorn Viruses are scrappy mischief-makers that spread their volatile (though tasty) element wherever they can.

Name: BrushMan
Description: A paintbrush Virus! BrushMan generates damage-halving holy sigils for its allies and dangerous terrain, like lava and poison, for its targets. Takes great pride in its art.

Name: Cloudy
Description: Cloudy Viruses spread nasty weather from above. If hit with electricity, they drop mighty lightning bolts.

Name: EleOgre
Description: A massive, floating ogre head that fires bolts of electricity from its horns. It also lays electrified tripwires to snare intruders.

Name: Jelly
Description: A big, rippling jellyfish that manipulates water, mud, lava, or whatever liquid is nearby.

Name: Lampy
Description: A gold oil lamp that that controls mist, Lampy Viruses protect allies and attack enemies with rolling, purple tides of mist.

Name: Mettaur
Description: Small and stout, Mettaurs mine data and Zenny with their pickaxes and hide under their helmets at the first sign of danger.

Name: MettaurΩ
Description: MettaurΩ’s small size hides its power. Its pickaxe cracks surfaces with its shockwaves.

Name: Mi2
Description: A cat-like Virus with a digital display helmet. It copies others’ elements and manipulates them. Its fur color changes with its element.

Name: Miney
Description: Miney Viruses lazily hop about, popping stealthy mines out of their slot-like mouths and laying them at key locations.

Name: Moloko
Description: Moloko Viruses scurry about, headbutting targets and spreading mounds of wool everywhere.

Name: Momogra
Description: The mischievous yet majestically moustached Momogra is a master mole miner.

Name: Null
Description: Null Viruses slowly lumber, their bits regenerating over time. They summon vortexes that slowly drag Navis in.

Name: Protecto
Description: A massive, unmoving pillar-like Virus that blocks access to areas and regenerates damage taken. They can be hacked to be moved.

Name: Puffball
Description: Puffballs use their masks like shields and wobble their arms, spreading poison clouds.

Name: Slimer
Description: A cute blob of slime that hides in pools of liquid before hopping out at targets and bodyslamming them.

Name: Viney
Description: Viney Viruses spread thorny vines everywhere, slipping between them and ensnaring targets.

Name: Volcano
Description: Volcano Viruses look like little volcanoes, scuttling on tiny feet and blasting massive fiery bursts from their tops to cover the area in lava.

Name: WindBox
Description: WindBoxes are fans that can blow mighty gusts of air at Navis or suck them in.

Name: Squeaker
Description: Squeakers are white ferret-like Viruses that sneak into places, grab shiny things, and then run off, leaving a trail of slippery soap.

Name: EggMecha
Description: EggMecha Viruses are agile gunners with jetpacks. Each has a captured Mr. Prog inside their chest that escapes on Virus deletion.

Name: ChaosBug
Description: A strange Virus with a fluid body. It grows stronger as it absorbs Mystery Data. Nobody knows where it comes from.

Name: Nabber
Description: Nabbers are hulking Viruses with huge nets on poles. They barge through walls and chase after Navis to steal their Zenny.

Name: Lunatic
Description: A pale white humanoid Virus with rabbit ears and glowing red eyes. Its body shimmers in the moonlight before disappearing from sight.

Name: SnoWing
Description: SnoWing Viruses look like prankster fairies, flying on low-poly wings and hurling icicles before disappearing into the mist.

Name: Spader
Description: A black-armored ranger with spade-tipped arrows. Its glowing eyes shine from within its helm, examining enemy attacks.

Name: HateMail
Description: HateMail Viruses look like innocuous piles of paper, stacked or strewn about. On close inspection, they’re covered in vile malware code.

Name: SatorIcon
Description: SatorIcon Viruses impersonate statues and other artworks, often with one detail askew. They telepathically communicate with others.

Name: Wikkid
Description: A small ghost Virus that puts wicked Marks on its enemies. After it’s deleted, it exacts its revenge.

Name: Headline
Description: Paparazzi Headline Viruses look like stout cameras in cheap, low-resolution suits. They use scandalizing “news” to protect themselves.

Name: Lurker
Description: Jet-black Lurkers have red amulets around their neck. They hunt Navis from the shadows, reappearing at vulnerable moments to strike.

Name: WillOWisp
Description: Malicious code come to life, WillOWisp Viruses live only to spread the wicked fire from their burning bodies.

Name: Ampy
Description: A tiny silver box with arms, legs, and a volume knob for a face. It can amplify things that shouldn’t be heard and mute things that should.

Name: MeloDeep
Description: A sea siren Virus with a beautiful harp. Its music has the power to save lives and dictate the tempo of battles.

Name: TaskManager
Description: TaskManagers are demonic Viruses with flaming whips. They cackle with glee as they whip other Viruses into shape.

Name: Amanojoker
Description: Dressed in black-white checkers, Amanojoker Viruses take joy in defying order, sowing chaos, and turning the internet upside-down.

Name: BlackBlossom
Description: A black flower Virus. Called “the Killer’s Corsage,” its aromas trick minds.

Name: CaskJeeves
Description: A spooky butler Virus that serves up cursed food from its spotless silver tray. When off duty, they rest in weathered wooden caskets.

Name: AnaPest
Description: AnaPests are big moth-like Viruses. Their paper wings are covered in poetry, author unknown. No two AnaPests have the same poems.

Name: BlotOut
Description: BlotOut Viruses are made of swirling ink and a large, slashing fountain pen. It curses letters and words to punish careless speakers.

Name: Delinquick
Description: The wiry Delinquick Virus rides a rocket motorcycle. Known for speeding off with stolen goods, another Virus can ride in the backseat.

Name: Choppy
Description: Choppy Viruses look like small military helicopters. Their floodlights intimidate targets and their bombs demolish anything in their way.

Name: Cleaner
Description: Cleaner Viruses look like giant sentient paint rollers. They sweep away art, elements, and damage to the area.

Name: SirenSong
Description: SirenSong Viruses look like huge alarm sirens with several bendy robotic arms. They toss their allies to swarm anyone that resists.

Name: UpDraft
Description: UpDraft Viruses are short broadcast towers with many megaphones and a flag on top. They send bodies to the front lines, willing or not.

Name: LurchingVoid
Description: A gigantic, amorphous Virus that sucks all light out of its surroundings. Survivors have only seen lashing limbs and gnashing maws.

Name: LurchingVoidΩ
Description: A gigantic, amorphous Virus that sucks all light out of its surroundings. Survivors have only seen lashing limbs and gnashing maws.

Name: Pariah
Description: Viruses made to resemble elegant statues, the Pariah hides in plain sight before tearing its unaware prey apart with supernatural speed.

Name: PariahΩ
Description: Viruses made to resemble elegant statues, the Pariah hides in plain sight before tearing its unaware prey apart with supernatural speed.

Name: WhiteMist
Description: Clouds of miniscule Viruses that infest and assimilate bodies. The telltale sign of infection is in the eyes. Is the host in there somewhere...?

Name: WhiteMistΩ
Description: Clouds of miniscule Viruses that infest and assimilate bodies. The telltale sign of infection is in the eyes. Is the host in there somewhere...?

Name: DustDevil
Description: DustDevil Viruses are tall, round, and metallic. They suck items and hazards into their body before launching them at high speeds.

Name: DustDevilΩ
Description: DustDevil Viruses are tall, round, and metallic. They suck items and hazards into their body before launching them at high speeds.

Name: HydraCannon
Description: HydraCannons are towering turrets, crackling with power. Their rotating barrels unleash a hailstorm of bullets on unlucky targets.

Name: HydraCannonΩ
Description: HydraCannons are towering turrets, crackling with power. Their rotating barrels unleash a hailstorm of bullets on unlucky targets.

Name: Scuttlest
Description: Scuttlests are insectoid Viruses based off a digital superweapon. They fire devastating lasers and manipulate protective barriers of light.

Name: ScuttlestΩ
Description: Scuttlests are insectoid Viruses based off a digital superweapon. They fire devastating lasers and manipulate protective barriers of light.

Name: SysCrasher
Description: The SysCrasher Virus looks like a hulking, glitchy mass, with 3 yellow eyes and skin like static. It uses voids to tear servers apart.

Name: SysCrasherΩ
Description: The SysCrasher Virus looks like a hulking, glitchy mass, with 3 yellow eyes and skin like static. It uses voids to tear servers apart.

Name: Heartbreaker
Description: The Heartbreaker is an elegant Virus dressed in flower-themed masquerade wear. It delights in turning friends against each other.

Name: HeartbreakerΩ
Description: The Heartbreaker is an elegant Virus dressed in flower-themed masquerade wear. It delights in turning friends against each other.

Name: Slashdance
Description: A cursed sword Virus! Slashdances’ runic malware can download ally elements, then punish enemies with air-cutting projectile slices.

Name: SlashdanceΩ
Description: A cursed sword Virus! Slashdances’ runic malware can download ally elements, then punish enemies with air-cutting projectile slices.

Name: Snugglebug
Description: An adorable, simple-minded, pillowy Virus that loves Navis. It has no idea that it invariably endangers its new friends. It just wants hugs.

Name: SnugglebugΩ
Description: An adorable, simple-minded, pillowy Virus that loves Navis. It has no idea that it invariably endangers its new friends. It just wants hugs.

Name: Wormore
Description: A writhing horde of large, shadowy, worm-like Viruses. They swallow and subsume everything in their path, always growing in numbers.

Name: WormoreΩ
Description: A writhing horde of large, shadowy, worm-like Viruses. They swallow and subsume everything in their path, always growing in numbers.

Name: Bladia
Description: These animated suits of armor ambush strong hosts to possess them. Unlucky victims are slowly drained of life unless rescued.

Name: BladiaΩ
Description: These animated suits of armor ambush strong hosts to possess them. Unlucky victims are slowly drained of life unless rescued.

Name: Double
Description: A wispy Virus able to bend its form. It scuttles around and hides in plain sight, waiting for unaware Navis to walk within slicing range.

Name: DoubleΩ
Description: A wispy Virus able to bend its form. It scuttles around and hides in plain sight, waiting for unaware Navis to walk within slicing range.

Name: Recycler
Description: A lurching Virus made of assimilated data, it shambles around in a vaguely humanoid form, leaving a trail of junk data in its wake.

Name: RecyclerΩ
Description: A lurching Virus made of assimilated data, it shambles around in a vaguely humanoid form, leaving a trail of junk data in its wake.

Name: RedColossus
Description: Slow and nearly-invincible, the RedColossus is towering and crystaline. It shakes the earth as it walks. Run. Don’t let it find you.

Name: RedColossusΩ
Description: Slow and nearly-invincible, the RedColossus is towering and crystaline. It shakes the earth as it walks. Run. Don’t let it find you.

Name: BulletExpress
Description: The speedy BulletExpress Virus looks like a train with a flaming smokestack. It hauls Viruses, hazards, and objects about at top speed.

Name: BulletExpressΩ
Description: The speedy BulletExpress Virus looks like a train with a flaming smokestack. It hauls Viruses, hazards, and objects about at top speed.

Name: NecroDancer
Description: A flashy Virus in glitzy clothes and grungy chains, it raises the dead with forbidden dances. Rumored to be an ascended Manneking.

Name: NecroDancerΩ
Description: A flashy Virus in glitzy clothes and grungy chains, it raises the dead with forbidden dances. Rumored to be an ascended Manneking.

Name: SpriteRip
Description: A small pixie Virus, the SpriteRip casts magic spells on its allies to bring out their inner power... regardless of whether they live to see it.

Name: SpriteRipΩ
Description: A small pixie Virus, the SpriteRip casts magic spells on its allies to bring out their inner power... regardless of whether they live to see it.

Name: Muramasa
Description: The Muramasa Virus is advanced metamorphic data. It shifts into the perfect weapon for its wielder, but power comes at a price...

Name: MuramasaΩ
Description: The Muramasa Virus is advanced metamorphic data. It shifts into the perfect weapon for its wielder, but power comes at a price...

Name: Anomaly
Description: A slim, lizard-like Virus with two pearl-white eyes. Its illusions and distractions can cause Navis to doubt everything - even themselves.

Name: AnomalyΩ
Description: A slim, lizard-like Virus with two pearl-white eyes. Its illusions and distractions can cause Navis to doubt everything - even themselves.

Name: Elemperor
Description: A mystic lamp Virus that rules over all elements. In spite of its majesty, it’s quite tiny.

Name: ElemperorΩ
Description: A mystic lamp Virus that rules over all elements. In spite of its majesty, it’s quite tiny.

Name: LostSol
Description: Based on ancient sun gods, the LostSol creates blinding light and scorching fire. Its heat can melt digital worlds and server hardware.

Name: LostSolΩ
Description: Based on ancient sun gods, the LostSol creates blinding light and scorching fire. Its heat can melt digital worlds and server hardware.

Name: Pseudomain
Description: A room-shaped Virus that tricks Navis into entering false doors. It can manipulate the shape and contents of the rooms within its body.

Name: PseudomainΩ
Description: A room-shaped Virus that tricks Navis into entering false doors. It can manipulate the shape and contents of the rooms within its body.

Name: HatTrick
Description: A wizard hat with lanky legs, it fills servers with fake objects and scares Navis with images of Viruses. What a nuisance!

Name: PartyAnimal
Description: PartyAnimal Viruses look like cartoon cats with big party hats. More chaotic than dangerous, they cover servers in party decorations.
